"a.健壮的，坚定的 【英】 adj.健壮的，坚定的( outstanding strength) 【考】 反义词：lank(瘦的) 【记】 stal(＝support)＋wa rt(＝worth)→值得依 靠的→坚定的 【例】 a stalwart ally(坚定的同盟者) adj. 身体健壮的; 坚定勇敢的 = stout 【记】sta站, l像枪, war战争, t他: 他站在那里拿着枪准备参加战争的样子是－坚定勇敢的, 身体健壮的 【参】stance(n 姿态; 站姿); standstill(n 停止; 停顿) 【类】constant: stalwart = judiciousness: sage不变的事物是坚定的 = 明智的人是贤明的 【反】lank(adj 瘦的; 细长的); timorous = timid(adj 胆小的) 【记】stall 畜栏 + war 战争，战争时畜栏里的战马都是健壮的；tall 高 + war 战争，长得高大打仗→健壮 【相关】stout 结实的, 勇敢坚定的 stalwart (adj.)  late 14c., ""resolute, determined,"" Scottish variant of stalworth, from Old English stælwierðe ""good, serviceable,"" probably a contracted compound of staðol ""base, foundation, support; stability, security"" (from Proto-Germanic *stathlaz, from PIE root *sta- ""to stand, set down, make or be firm;"" see stet) + wierðe ""good, excellent, worthy"" (see worth). Another theory traces the first element of stælwierðe to Old English stæl ""place,"" from Proto-Germanic *stælaz."
